        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 2:58PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 258 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Steens, or 7 miles west of Millport, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Millport, Kennedy, and Melborne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
